obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (8090)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8090&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Sikh Gurdwaras`
  line `Act, 1971.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 7th April, 1972, vide notification No. G.S.R. 241(E), dated 7th April, 1972, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3 (i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (8091)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8091&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) “appointed day” means the date on which this Act shall come into force;`
  line
  line `(b) “Board” means the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Board constituted under section 3 of the Delhi Sikh`
  line `Gurdwaras (Management) Act, 1971 (24 of 1971);`
  line
  line `(c) “Committee” means the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Management Committee established under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) “Delhi” means the Union territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(e) “Director Gurdwara Elections” means the Director Gurdwara Elections appointed by the`
  line `Central Government under section 13;`
  line
  line `(f) “Gurdwaras” means the Sikh Gurdwaras situated in Delhi as were, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, being managed by or affiliated to the Board and includes such other local Gurdwaras`
  line `as may, after the appointed day, be affiliated to or managed by the Committee;`
  line
  line `(g) “Gurdwara property” means,—`
  line
  line `(i) all movable and immovable property which, immediately before the appointed day, vested`
  line `or was kept in deposit in the name of the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) all property which stands in the name of the Gurdwaras or in the name of the Board or the`
  line `present or old managers of the historic Gurdwaras;`
  line
  line `(iii) all offerings in cash or kind made in various Gurdwaras or institutions managed or`
  line `controlled by the Committee;`
  line
  line `(iv) all property in cash or kind, movable as well as immovable that may be acquired by`
  line `purchase, exchange or otherwise by the Gurdwaras, or the Committee, from time to time;`
  line
  line `(v) all grants, donations or contributions made, from time to time, by any person or authority`
  line `to the Gurdwaras or the Committee,`
  line
  line `and includes any actionable claim with respect to such Gurdwara property;`
  line
  line `(h) “local Gurdwara” means a Gurdwara in Delhi, other than a Gurdwara under the control or`
  line `management of the Board immediately before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(i) a person shall not be deemed to be “ordinarily resident” in a ward on the ground only that he`
  line `owns or is in possession of a dwelling-house therein and a person absenting himself temporarily from`
  line `his place of ordinary residence shall not by reason thereof cease to be ordinarily resident therein;`
  line
  line `(j) “patit” means a Sikh who trims or shaves his beard or hair (keshas) or who after taking Amrit`
  line `commits any one or more of the four Kurahitis;`
  line
  line `(k) “registered Singh Sabha” means a Singh Sabha registered as a society under the Societies`
  line `Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), which is managing or controlling a local Gurdwara in Delhi;`
  line
  line `(l) “regulation” means a regulation made under this Act by the Committee;`
  line
  line `(m) “rule” means a rule made under this Act by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(n) “Sikh” means a person who professes the Sikh religion, believes and follows the teachings of`
  line `Sri Guru Granth Sahib and the ten Gurus only and keeps unshorn hair (Keshas). For the purposes of if`
  line `any question arises as to whether any living person is or is not a Sikh, he shall be deemed respectively`
  line `to be or not to be a Sikh according as he makes or refuses to make in the manner prescribed by rules`
  line `the following declaration:—`
  line
  line `“I solemnly affirm that I am a Keshadhari Sikh, that I believe in and follow the teachings of Sri`
  line `Guru Granth Sahib and the ten Gurus only, and that I have no other religion.”;`
  line
  line `(o) “Amritdhari Sikh” means and includes every Sikh who has taken Khande ka Amrit or Khanda`
  line `Pahul, prepared and administered according to the tenets of Sikh religion and rites at the hands of five`
  line `Pyaras or “beloved ones”.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (8092)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Incorporation of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8092&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established a Committee to be called`
  line `the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Management Committee for the proper management and control of the`
  line `Gurdwaras and Gurdwara property.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal and shall by such name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall have its head office in Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (8093)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8093&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Committee shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) forty-six members to be elected from various wards into which Delhi shall be divided in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) nine members to be co-opted by the elected members of the Committee referred to in`
  line `clause (a) in the manner hereinafter appearing,—`
  line
  line `(i) two members to represent the registered Singh Sabhas of Delhi who shall be chosen by`
  line `drawing of lots out of the Presidents of those registered Singh Sabhas;`
  line
  line `(ii) four members, each being the head priest of the (1) Sri Akal Takhat Sahib, Amritsar,`
  line `(2) Sri Takhat Kesgarh Sahib, Anandpur, (3) Sri Takhat Patna Sahib, Patna, and (4) Sri Takhat`
  line `Hazur Sahib, Nanded:`
  line
  line `Provided that the head priest shall have no right to vote for the purpose of election of`
  line `office-bearers and other members of the Executive Board under sub-section (1) and sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(iii) one member, being the nominee of the Shromani Gurdwara Parbandhak Committee,`
  line Amritsar;
  line
  line `(iv) two members to represent the Sikh community of Delhi, other than those referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (i), sub-clause (ii) and sub-clause (iii), to be chosen in accordance with the system of`
  line `proportional representation by means of a single transferable vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (8094)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8094&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of a member of`
  line `the Committee shall be four years and shall commence from the date on which the first meeting of the`
  line `Committee is held under section 15, and no longer.`
  line
  line `(2) When a vacancy occurs in the Committee owing to death, resignation, removal or otherwise of a`
  line `member, a new member shall be elected or co-opted, as the case may be, in the manner in which the`
  line `member whose seat is to be filled was elected or co-opted and every such member shall continue to hold`
  line `office so long only as the member in whose place he is elected or co-opted would have been entitled to`
  line `hold office, if the vacancy had not occurred.`
  line
  line `(3) An outgoing member shall continue in office until the notification of election or co-option of his`
  line `successor is published under section 12.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (8095)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Delimitation of wards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8095&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of election of members of the Committee, Delhi shall`
  line `be divided into single member wards.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director Gurdwara Elections shall by order determine—`
  line
  line `(a) the number of wards; and`
  line
  line `(b) the extent of each ward.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director Gurdwara Elections may, from time to time, in consultation with the Committee,`
  line `alter or amend any order made under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (8096)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Electoral roll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8096&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) An electoral roll shall be prepared in such manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `rules for every ward notified under section 6 on which shall be entered the names of all persons entitled to`
  line `be registered as voters in that ward.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for any ward more than once.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for more than one ward.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (8097)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Qualifications of elector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8097&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every person who--`
  line
  line `(a) has been ordinarily resident in a ward for not less than one hundred and eighty days during the`
  line `qualifying period,`
  line
  line `(b) is a Sikh of not less than twenty-one years of age on the qualifying date,`
  line
  line `shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for that ward:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be registered as an elector who--`
  line
  line `(a) trims or shaves his beard or keshas;`
  line
  line `(b) smokes;`
  line
  line `(c) takes alcoholic drinks.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, the "qualifying date" and the "qualifying period"--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of electoral rolls first prepared under this Act, shall be the 1st day of January, 1972,`
  line `and the period beginning on the 1st day of January, 1971 and ending on the 31st day of`
  line `December, 1971, respectively; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of every electoral roll subsequently prepared under this Act, shall be the 1st day of`
  line `January of the year in which it is prepared and the year immediately preceding that year respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (8098)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Right to vote.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8098&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every person registered on the electoral roll for the time being in force for any`
  line `ward for the election of a member of the Committee, shall be entitled while so registered to vote at an`
  line `election of a member for that ward, provided that no person shall be entitled to vote at an election in more`
  line `than one ward.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (8099)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Qualifications of member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8099&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be qualified to be chosen or co-opted as a`
  line `member of the Committee if such person—`
  line
  line `(a) has not attained the age of twenty-five years;`
  line
  line `(b) is not a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of an elected member, if he is not registered as an elector in the electoral roll for`
  line `any ward;`
  line
  line `(d) is not an Amritdhari Sikh;`
  line
  line `(e) being an Amritdhari Sikh, trims or shaves his beard or keshas;`
  line
  line `(f) takes alcoholic drinks;`
  line
  line `(g) smokes;`
  line
  line `(h) is a patit;`
  line
  line `(i) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(j) is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(k) has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude or has been dismissed from`
  line `service by Government, Board, Committee or any local authority, on account of moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(l) is a paid servant of any Gurdwara or a local Gurdwara;`
  line
  line `(m) not being a blind person cannot ^1`
  line `[read and write] Gurmukhi.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A person shall be deemed to—`
  line
  line `(i) be able to read Gurmukhi if he is able to recite Sri Guru Granth Sahib, in Gurmukhi, and`
  line
  line `(ii) write Gurmukhi if he fills his nomination paper for election to the Committee in Gurmukhi in`
  line `his own handwriting.`
  line
  line `If any question arises whether a candidate is or is not able to read and write Gurmukhi, the question`
  line `shall be decided in such manner as may be ^2`
  line `[prescribed by rules].`
  line
  line `(2) If a person sits or votes as a member of the Committee when he knows that he is not qualified for`
  line `such membership, he shall be liable in respect of each day on which he so sits or votes to a penalty of`
  line `three hundred rupees which shall be recoverable as an arrear of land revenue`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1974, s. 2, for "read or write" (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "prescribed by regulations" (w.e.f. 23-9-1974)`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (8100)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Elections.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8100&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Election of members under clause (a) of section 4 whether for the purpose of initial`
  line `constitution of the Committee under section 3, or for filling vacancies arising by efflux of time or a casual`
  line `vacancy, shall be conducted by the Director Gurdwara Elections in accordance with the rules made in this`
  line `behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election shall be held to fill a casual vacancy occurring within four months prior to`
  line `the holding of a general election under this section`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (8101)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Publication of results.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8101&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The names of all persons elected as members of the Committee`
  line `shall, as soon as may be, after such election be published by the Director Gurdwara Elections in the`
  line `manner prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) The names of all persons co-opted as members under clause (b) of section 4 shall likewise be`
  line `published by the Director Gurdwara Elections in the manner prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (8102)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Director Gurdwara Elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8102&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint a suitable person to be the Director Gurdwara Elections in whom shall vest the`
  line `superintendence, direction and control of the preparation of electoral rolls for, and the conduct of,`
  line `elections of members of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as Director Gurdwara Elections unless he is a`
  line `citizen of India and possesses judicial or administrative experience for a period of not less than ten years`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 37, the term of office, and the terms and conditions of service`
  line `of the Director Gurdwara Elections shall be such as may be prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (8103)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `First meeting of the elected members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8103&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons to be co-opted as members of the`
  line `Committee under clause (b), of section 4 shall be chosen at the first meeting of the elected members`
  line `which shall be convened by the Director Gurdwara Elections as early as possible and not later than fifteen`
  line `days after publication of the results of the election under sub-section (1) of section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director Gurdwara Elections may adjourn the first meeting of the elected members to any`
  line `other date or dates, being not later than fifteen days from the date of the first meeting aforesaid, if the`
  line `elected members are unable to choose all persons to be co-opted at that first meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (8104)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `First meeting of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8104&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director Gurdwara Elections shall summon the first`
  line `meeting of the Committee to meet on such date, not being later than fifteen days after the publication of`
  line `the names of the members co-opted under sub-section (2) of section 12, as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The first meeting shall be held at such time and place as the Director Gurdwara Elections may`
  line `appoint and shall be presided by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that while so presiding at the meeting of the Committee, the Director Gurdwara Elections`
  line `shall have no right to vote.`
  line
  line `(3) Every member of the Committee shall, before taking his seat make and subscribe before the`
  line `Director Gurdwara Elections an oath according to the form set out for the purpose in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(4) The members of the Committee shall proceed thereafter to elect from amongst themselves a`
  line `pro tempore Chairman in such manner as may be prescribed by rules, who shall preside at the meeting`
  line `until the Committee elects the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (8105)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Election of office bearers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8105&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall, at its first meeting after the election of the`
  line `pro tempore Chairman under sub-section (4) of section 15, elect from amongst its members a President,`
  line `who shall conduct the election of other office-bearers and members of the Executive Board under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall also at its first meeting elect from amongst its members a Senior`
  line `Vice-President, Junior Vice-President, General Secretary and a Joint Secretary (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `office-bearers of the Committee), and shall also at the same meeting in like manner elect ten of its`
  line `members to be members of the Executive Board of the Committee, and the office-bearers and members so`
  line `elected shall be the Executive Board of the Committee.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) No member of the Committee shall, at the same time, hold any of the offices referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in more than one capacity.`
  line
  line `(5) The President and other members of the Executive Board elected under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) shall hold office for a term of one year but shall be eligible for re-election for one more`
  line `term only:`
  line
  line `Provided that an outgoing office-bearer or member shall continue in office until election of his`
  line `successor is held.`
  line
  line `(6) The election of the President and other office-bearers and members of the Executive Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or any subsequent annual election to any of those offices shall be held`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of sub-section (2) of section 5 shall apply so far as may be to the filling of a casual`
  line `vacancy in the ^2[office of the President, any other office-bearer or member of the Executive Board] as`
  line `they apply in relation to casual vacancies in the membership of the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 6 of 1981, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-1-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1974, s. 3, for "membership of the Executive Board" (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (8106)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to convene another meeting for election of office-bearers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1974, s. 4 (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8106&sectionno=16A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[16A. Power to convene another meeting for election of office-bearers.—If the Committee at its`
  line `first meeting is unable to elect a pro tempore Chairman or a President or any other office-bearer or`
  line `member of the Executive Board under sub-section (4) of section 15 or sub-section (1) or sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 16, the Director Gurdwara Elections shall summon another meeting of the Committee, being`
  line `not later than fifteen days from the date of the first meeting, for the election of the pro tempore Chairman,`
  line `the President or the remaining office-bearers or members of the Executive Board, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 15 and 16 shall, so far as may be, apply to the conduct of election`
  line `under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (8107)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Vacation, resignation and removal of members and office-bearers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8107&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member of the`
  line `Committee may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the President.`
  line
  line `(2) An office-bearer or any other member of the Executive Board--`
  line
  line `(a) shall vacate his office if he ceases to be a member of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) may at any time by writing under his hand addressed to the Committee resign his office; and`
  line
  line `(c) may be removed from his office by a resolution of the Committee passed by a three-fourth`
  line `majority of the total members thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that no resolution for the purpose of clause (c) shall be moved unless it is supported by not`
  line `less than seventeen members of the Committee and fourteen days notice has been given of their intention`
  line `to move the resolution.`
  line
  line `(3) The resignation of office under sub-section (1) or clause (b) of sub-section (2) shall be effective`
  line `from the date from which it is accepted by the Executive Board or the Committee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (8108)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Fees and allowances of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8108&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Any office-bearer or other member of the Executive Board`
  line `or any other member of the Committee may, if he so desires, draw such fees and allowances for attending`
  line `the meetings of the Executive Board or the Committee and for attending to any other work of the`
  line `Executive Board or the Committee, as the case may be, as may be prescribed by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (8109)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Meetings of the Committee and the Executive Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8109&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual general meeting of the`
  line `Committee shall be held in every year.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Board shall meet at least once in every fortnight or at such intervals as may be`
  line `prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The President, or in his absence the Senior Vice-President and in the absence of both, the Junior`
  line `Vice-President, and in the absence of all the three, any other member elected from amongst themselves`
  line `shall preside at any meeting of the Committee or of the Executive Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee or the Executive Board shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to`
  line `transaction of the business at its meetings as may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) Save as otherwise provided, all questions which come up before any meeting of the Committee or`
  line `the Executive Board shall be decided by a majority of votes of the members present and voting and in the`
  line `event of equality of votes, the person presiding shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(6) All proceedings of the meetings of the Committee or the Executive Board shall be recorded in`
  line `Punjabi in Gurmukhi script`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (8110)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title Sub-committees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8110&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive Board may constitute such number of sub-committees from`
  line `amongst the members of the Committee as it thinks fit and for such purpose as it may decide.`
  line
  line `(2) A sub-committee constituted under sub-section (1) shall meet at such time and places and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be`
  line `prescribed by regulations`
  line
  line `(3) A member of a sub-committee may, if he so desires, draw such fees and allowances for attending`
  line `its meetings and for attending to any other work of the sub-committee, as may be prescribed by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (8111)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Powers of the Executive Board and its office-bearers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8111&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive Board shall exercise`
  line `on behalf of the Committee all powers conferred on the Committee by the provisions of this Act which`
  line `are not expressly reserved to be exercised by the Committee in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The President or any other office-bearer of the Executive Board may exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties as may be prescribed by regulations or as may, from time to time, be delegated by the`
  line `Executive Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the President may, on`
  line `his own motion or otherwise, after calling the record of any case, revise any order passed by any authority`
  line `to whom such powers have been delegated by the Executive Board and—`
  line
  line `(i) confirm, modify or set aside the order,`
  line
  line `(ii) impose any penalty or set aside, reduce, confirm or enhance the penalty imposed upon any`
  line `employee of the Committee,`
  line
  line `(iii) remit the case to the authority which made the order or to any other authority directing such`
  line `further action or inquiry as considered proper in the circumstances of the case, or`
  line
  line `(iv) pass such other orders as he deems fit.`
  line
  line `(4) No order passed by the President under sub-section (3) shall be enforced unless and until it is`
  line `confirmed by the Executive Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (8112)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Validity of acts of Committee, Executive Board or sub-committees not to be questioned by reason of vacancy, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8112&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Committee or the Executive Board or any`
  line `sub-committee shall be invalidated by reason only of the existence of any vacancy amongst its members`
  line `or any defect in the constitution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (8113)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Officers and other employees of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8113&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee may appoint such`
  line `number of officers and other employees as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of its`
  line `functions, and may, from time to time, determine the number, designations, grades and scales of pay or`
  line `other remuneration of the officers and other employees, and may at any time reduce, suspend, remove or`
  line `dismiss or impose any other penalty on any officer or other employee for carelessness, unfitness, neglect`
  line `of duty or other misconduct.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees appointed under sub-section (1) shall exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties as may be prescribed by regulations or as may, from time to time, be delegated by the`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions of service of the officers and other employees shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (8114)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Powers and functions of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8114&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules`
  line `made thereunder, the control, direction and general superintendence over all the Gurdwaras and Gurdwara`
  line `property in Delhi shall vest in the Committee, and it shall be the duty of the Committee—`
  line
  line `(i) to arrange for the proper performance of the religious rites and ceremonies in the Gurdwaras,`
  line
  line `(ii) to provide facilities for worship by the devotees at the Gurdwaras,`
  line
  line `(iii) to ensure safe custody of its funds, movable and immovable properties, deposits, offerings in`
  line `cash or kind,`
  line
  line `(iv) to do all such things as may be incidental and conducive to the efficient management of the`
  line `affairs of Gurdwaras, educational and other institutions under the Committee and their properties or`
  line `to the convenience of devotees,`
  line
  line `(v) to provide suitable accommodation and facilities for pilgrims,`
  line
  line `(vi) to maintain free langars,`
  line
  line `(vii) to manage the historic and other Gurdwaras, educational and other institutions and their`
  line `properties in such a way as to make them inspiring centres of the Sikh tradition, culture and religion,`
  line
  line `(viii) to ensure maintenance of order, discipline and proper hygienic conditions in Gurdwaras,`
  line `educational and other institutions under its management,`
  line
  line `(ix) to open free dispensaries,`
  line
  line `(x) to spread education, especially the knowledge of Punjabi, in Gurmukhi script,`
  line
  line `(xi) to establish educational institutions, research centres and libraries.`
  line
  line `(xii) to render financial assistance to religious and educational institutions, societies and needy`
  line persons,
  line
  line `(xiii) to give stipends to needy and deserving students,`
  line
  line `(xiv) to render help in the case of the uplift of the Sikh community and propagation of Sikh`
  line religion,
  line
  line `(xv) to perform such other functions and to do such religious or charitable acts, as may be`
  line `prescribed by regulations for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (8115)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Gurdwara Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8115&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Gurdwara Fund and all receipts and income of the`
  line `Gurdwaras and of the Gurdwara property (including all amounts comprised for the time being in`
  line `Gurdwara property) shall be credited thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gurdwara Fund shall be held by the Committee in trust for the purposes of this Act subject to`
  line `the provisions herein contained and shall not be utilised for any purpose other than the one authorised by`
  line `this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) All expenses incurred or payments or disbursements to be made, by the Committee in the`
  line `discharge of its functions under this Act shall be made from the Gurdwara Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (8116)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Prohibition regarding making of contributions for political purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8116&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in`
  line `this Act shall, or shall be deemed to authorise the Committee to contribute any amount or amounts—`
  line
  line `(a) to any political party, or`
  line
  line `(b) for the benefit of any political party, or`
  line
  line `(c) for any political purpose to any individual or body`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (8117)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8117&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) In respect of every financial year, budget (annual financial statement) of the`
  line `estimated receipts and expenditure of the Committee for the year shall be placed before the Committee`
  line `and duly passed.`
  line
  line `(2) No moneys out of the Gurdwara Fund shall be appropriated except as passed and approved by the`
  line Committee.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (8118)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Maintenance of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8118&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall maintain proper accounts showing receipts`
  line `on account of and expenditure out of Gurdwara Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) At the end of each calendar month, a statement of income and expenditure relating to that month`
  line `shall be prepared and placed before the Committee and it shall be pasted at prominent places outside all`
  line `Gurdwaras; and a consolidated annual statement, showing income and expenditure relating to a financial`
  line `year shall likewise be prepared and placed before the Committee and outside the Gurdwaras at the end of`
  line `each financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (8119)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Audit of Accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8119&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of the Committee including those of the Gurdwaras, and`
  line `Gurdwara property including educational and other charitable institutions administered by the Committee,`
  line `shall be audited by one or more auditors duly qualified to act as auditor under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) (hereinafter referred to as the auditor), who shall be`
  line `appointed by the Committee within sixty days of the close of every financial year and shall receive such`
  line `remuneration as the Committee may fix:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first appointment of auditors shall be made by the Committee within sixty days`
  line `from the date of its first meeting held under section 15.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of any such audit and examination of accounts the auditors may, by a demand in`
  line `writing, require from the Committee or any office-bearer or member or employee of the Committee or`
  line `any Gurdwara, educational or other institution of the Committee, the production before him of all books,`
  line `deeds, vouchers and all other documents and papers which he deems necessary, and may require any`
  line `person holding or accountable for any such books, deeds, vouchers, documents and papers to appear`
  line `before him at any audit and examination, to answer all questions which may be put to him with respect to`
  line `the same or to prepare and submit any further statement which such auditor may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) Within thirty days after the audit and examination have been completed, the auditor shall submit a`
  line `report to the Committee upon each account audited and examined.`
  line
  line `(4) The audit report shall be published in, at least two daily papers of Delhi (one in English and one in`
  line `Punjabi) as well as in Gurdwara Journal, if any, within thirty days of its receipt.`
  line
  line `(5) The report of the auditor shall, among other matters, specify all items of expenditure which in his`
  line `opinion are illegal, irregular or improper, all cases of failure of recoveries of money or property due to the`
  line `Committee, all instances of loss or wasteful expenditure of money or property due to negligence or`
  line `misconduct and all instances in which any money or property has been devoted to any purpose not`
  line `authorised by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (8120)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Consideration of the auditor’s report by the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8120&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Committee, in meeting next`
  line `following the date of receipt of the auditors report, shall consider such report and satisfy itself that no`
  line `expenditure shown therein has been incurred otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Act`
  line `and shall pass such orders as are, in its opinion, necessary and proper to rectify the illegal, unauthorised or`
  line `improper expenditure and may also pass such further orders upon the report, as it may deem proper:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the next meeting falls on a day earlier than two months after the receipt of the report`
  line `it may be considered in the meeting next following which shall be convened before the expiry of a period`
  line `of three months from the date of receipt of the said report.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (8121)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Election disputes, electoral offences etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8121&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, 20, 22,`
  line `23, 24, 25, 27, 28, 29 and 30 of the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957), shall mutatis`
  line `mutandis apply, subject to such modifications as the Central Government may by order direct, in relation`
  line `to settlement of disputes regarding elections, corrupt practices and electoral offences in respect of election`
  line `or co-option of members of the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (8122)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Jurisdiction of District Court in other matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Clauses (a) and (b) omitted by Act 46 of 1974, s. 5 (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8122&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Court of the District Judge in Delhi shall`
  line `also have jurisdiction in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) Petitions regarding complaints, irregularities, breach of trust, mismanagement in any`
  line `Gurdwara, educational or other institutions against any member, office-bearer or officer or other`
  line `employee of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(d) Petitions arising out of any type of disputes between the Committee and its employees`
  line `including past employees.`
  line
  line `(e) Applications regarding failure of publication of, or non-implementation or non-clearance of`
  line `the objections raised in, any annual report of the auditors of the Committee`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (8123)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8123&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order passed by the District Judge may, within sixty`
  line `days of the order, prefer an appeal to the High Court at Delhi and the orders of the High Court on such`
  line `appeal shall be final and conclusive.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 5 and 12 of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply to appeals under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (8124)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Procedure for affiliation of local Gurdwaras.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8124&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered Singh Sabha may, in relation to`
  line `any local Gurdwara under its control, decide by a resolution adopted by three-fourth majority of its total`
  line `membership for affiliating that local Gurdwara to the Committee and if the Committee consents thereto,`
  line `the said local Gurdwara shall be deemed to be affiliated to the Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) All assets and liabilities of the local Gurdwara so affiliated and of the registered Singh Sabha shall`
  line `thereafter vest in the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (8125)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Act not to affect rites and practices of Sikh religion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8125&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force shall—`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder,`
  line `affect any honour, emolument or perquisite to which any person is entitled by custom or otherwise in`
  line `any Gurdwara;`
  line
  line `(b) authorise any interference with the religious or spiritual functions performed in any`
  line Gurdwara.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (8126)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Members, officers and other employees to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8126&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the`
  line `Committee, the Executive Board, or any sub-committee, the Director Gurdwara Elections and every other`
  line `officer and employee of the Committee shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (8127)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Salary, etc., of the Director Gurdwara Elections to be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India in the first instance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8127&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The salaries and allowances payable to the Director Gurdwara`
  line `Elections or to the officers and other employees engaged for the conduct of elections to the Committee,`
  line `shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India in the first instance, but shall be recoverable from`
  line `the Committee by debit to the Gurdwara Fund after the close of each financial year.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sum due to the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall, if not paid within three`
  line `months after the demand has been made, be recoverable as arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (8128)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Protection of action taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8128&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall lie against any`
  line `member of the Committee, the Executive Board or any sub-committee, the Director Gurdwara Elections`
  line `or any other officer or employee of the Committee for anything which is in good faith done or intended to`
  line `be done under this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (8129)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8129&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for or regulate all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which a declaration for the purpose of clause (n) of section 2 shall be made;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(aa) the manner and the criterion for deciding whether a candidate for election as a member of`
  line `the Committee is able to read and write Gurmukhi;]`
  line
  line `(b) the particulars to be entered in the electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(c) the preliminary publication of electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which and the time within which claims and objections as to entries in electoral`
  line `rolls may be preferred;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which notices of claims or objections shall be published;`
  line
  line `(f) the place, date and time at which claims or objections shall be heard and the manner in which`
  line `claims or objections shall be heard and disposed of;`
  line
  line `(g) the final publication of electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(h) the revision and correction of electoral rolls and inclusion of names therein;`
  line
  line `(i) the appointment of returning officers, assistant returning Officers, Presiding officers and`
  line `polling officers for the conduct of elections;`
  line
  line `(j) the nomination of candidates, form of nomination papers, objections to nominations and`
  line `scrutiny of nominations;`
  line
  line `(k) the deposits to be made by candidates, time and manner of making such deposits and the`
  line `circumstances under which such deposits may be refunded to candidates or forfeited to the`
  line Committee;
  line
  line `(l) the withdrawal of candidatures;`
  line
  line `(m) the appointment of agents of candidates;`
  line
  line `(n) the procedure in contested and uncontested elections;`
  line
  line `(o) the date, time and place for poll and other matters relating to the conduct of elections`
  line including—
  line
  line `(i) the appointment of polling stations for each ward,`
  line
  line `(ii) the hours during which the polling station shall be kept open for the casting of votes,`
  line
  line `(iii) the printing and issue of ballot papers,`
  line
  line `(iv) the checking of voters by reference to the electoral roll,`
  line
  line `(v) the marking with indelible ink of the left forefinger or any other finger or limb of the voter`
  line `and prohibition of the delivery of any ballot paper to any person if at the time such person applies`
  line `for such paper he has already such mark so as to prevent personation of voters,`
  line
  line `(vi) the manner in which votes are to be given and in particular in the case of illiterate voters`
  line `or of voters under physical or other disability,`
  line
  line `(vii) the procedure to be followed in respect of challenging votes and tendered votes,`
  line
  line `(viii) the scrutiny of votes, counting of votes, the declaration of the results and the procedure`
  line `in case of equality of votes or in the event of a member being elected to represent more than one`
  line ward,
  line
  line `(ix) the custody and disposal of papers relating to elections,`
  line
  line `(x) the suspension of polls in case of any interruption by riot, violence or any other sufficient`
  line `cause and the holding of a fresh poll,`
  line
  line `(xi) the holding of a fresh poll in the case of destruction of, or tampering with, ballot boxes`
  line `before the count,`
  line
  line `(xii) the countermanding of the poll in the case of the death of a candidate before the poll;`
  line
  line `(p) the fee to be paid on an election petition;`
  line
  line `(q) the terms and conditions of service of the Director Gurdwara Elections;`
  line
  line `(r) the procedure for the election of pro tempore Chairman under sub-section (4) of section 15,`
  line `and of the President and other office-bearers and members of the Executive Board under section 16;`
  line
  line `(s) any other matter in respect of which the Central Government deems it necessary to make rules`
  line `under this section or in respect of which this Act makes no provision or makes insufficient provision`
  line `and provision is, in the opinion of the Central Government, necessary;`
  line
  line `(t) the manner in which results of election or co-option of members of the Committee shall be`
  line `published, or the orders made under the rules shall be widely made known by affixing copies thereof`
  line `in conspicuous public places, by publishing the same by beat of drum or by advertisement in local`
  line newspapers.
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule under this section the Central Government may provide that any contravention`
  line `thereof shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine or`
  line `with both.`
  line
  line `(4) All rules made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after they are made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in ^2`
  line `[two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,] both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rules or both Houses agree that the rules should not be made, the rules shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under those rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1974, s. 6 (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1974, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 23-9-1974)`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (8130)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of Committee to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8130&sectionno=40&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee may make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder for carrying out its functions`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) fees and allowances to which office-bearers and other members of the Executive Board or`
  line `other members of the Committee or of a sub-committee shall be entitled for attending meetings or any`
  line `other work of the Executive Board, Committee or sub-committee respectively;`
  line
  line `(c) the periods of interval at which meetings of the Executive Board shall be held, the manner in`
  line `which meetings of the Committee or the Executive Board or any sub-committee shall be convened,`
  line `the quorum for the transaction of business thereat and the rules of procedure to be followed for`
  line `transaction of business at meetings of the Committee, the Executive Board or any sub-committee;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which a majority decision of the Executive Board shall be obtained by`
  line `circulation to its office-bearers and members of any matter requiring decision;`
  line
  line `(e) the matters in respect of which powers may be exercised or duties performed by the President`
  line `or other office-bearers of the Executive Board or by any officer or other employee of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(f) the terms and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Committee`
  line `including recruitment, transfer, fixation of seniority, promotion of, and disciplinary action or`
  line `punishment against, such officers and other employees;`
  line
  line `(g) any other functions or religious or charitable acts which, in addition to those specified in`
  line `section 24, may be performed or done by the Committee, and the conditions and restrictions subject`
  line `to which those functions or acts shall be performed or done;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which cash or other moneys of the Gurdwara Fund shall be deposited or`
  line invested;
  line
  line `(i) the form in which the budget of the Committee shall be presented;`
  line
  line `(j) the form in which the accounts of the Committee shall be maintained and the publication of`
  line `such accounts;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which any regulations or orders made thereunder shall be published or widely`
  line `made known by affixing copies thereof in conspicuous public places, by publishing the same by beat`
  line `of drum or by advertisement in local newspapers;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (a) omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (8131)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 42
  title `Repeal and Saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223&sectionId=8131&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00017_197182_1517807320223
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the date of the establishment of the Committee, the Delhi Sikh`
  line `Gurdwaras (Management) Act, 1971 (24 of 1971), shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,—`
  line
  line `(a) any appointment, notification, order or rule made or issued under the said Act shall, in so far`
  line `as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue in force and be deemed to have been`
  line `made or issued under the provisions of this Act unless and until it is superseded by any appointment,`
  line `notification, order or rule made or issued under the said provisions;`
  line
  line `(b) all budget estimates made, all obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts entered into`
  line `and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Board shall be`
  line `deemed to have been made, incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by, with or for the`
  line `Committee under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all Gurdwara property, movable and immovable and all interests of whatsoever nature and`
  line `kind therein vested in, belonging or due to, the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Board, immediately before such`
  line `establishment, shall, with all rights, powers and privileges of whatsoever description, used, enjoyed or`
  line `possessed by the Board, vest in the Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) all sums of money including rents due to the Board immediately before such establishment`
  line `shall be deemed to be due to the Committee;`
  line
  line `(e) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which might have been instituted by or`
  line `against the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Board may be continued or instituted by or against the Committee;`
  line
  line `(f) any will deed or other instrument which contains any bequest, gifts or trusts in favour of the`
  line `Board shall as from such establishment, be construed as if the Committee were therein named instead`
  line `of the said Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
